body:
ONNX Runtime React Native supports only ort format model, not onnx model to reduce binary size in mobile devices. If your model is onnx, you can convert to ort referring to https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/tutorials/mobile/model-conversion.html#converting-onnx-models-to-ort-format.

And, you can also check [operator and type support](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/tree/master/js/react_native#operator-and-type-support) since onnxruntime-react-native is using pre-built onnxruntime mobile package and there are some restriction on supporting operators or versions.
